gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 109, Timberwolves 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bulls defeated the Timberwolves, 109-101. DeMar DeRozan led Chicago with 27 points and eight assists as Alex Caruso totaled 21 points and a career-best seven 3PM, along with five rebounds, and five assists. Anthony Edwards (22 points, 11 rebounds, five assists) and Rudy Gobert (19 points on 8-8 FG, 10 rebounds) led Minnesota in the loss. Chicago improves to 36-39 on the year as Minnesota has a 4-game win streak snapped, moving to 51-23 on the year.
